This paper focuses on the design of an efficient channel acquisition method for a wireless energy transfer (WET) system, which involves multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) communication and optimization of energy harvesting. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the study of communication systems and their fundamental limits. The paper also discusses the practical implementation of WET in wireless networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the optimization problem formulation and closed-form solutions indicate that the paper could be relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.MM (Multimedia), which deal with the design and analysis of complex systems and multimedia processing, respectively. Finally, the paper's focus on energy harvesting and optimization suggests that it could also belong to cs.PE (Performance).
